WEBVTT

00:02.420 --> 00:04.251
CLAIRE: Previously on Heroes.

00:04.338 --> 00:05.418
What happened
to your parents?

00:05.506 --> 00:07.588
I touched them and they died.

00:07.675 --> 00:08.755
MR. BENNET: I know
about your power.

00:08.843 --> 00:10.754
And I know that
you're not a killer.

00:10.845 --> 00:11.880
You're a healer.

00:11.971 --> 00:13.086
You're staying here?

00:13.222 --> 00:15.463
How long?
Until I know that
you're all right.

00:15.933 --> 00:17.139
I'm Becky Taylor.

00:17.226 --> 00:19.342
Open rush starts
today at the house,

00:19.437 --> 00:21.098
why don't you come by
and meet the girls?

00:23.065 --> 00:25.192
I'm missing bid night,
Uncle Samuel.

00:25.276 --> 00:27.358
Checking on your work
with Claire Bennet.

00:27.445 --> 00:29.777
You’re doing everything
you can to isolate her,

00:29.864 --> 00:32.981
push other people away,
push her in our direction?

00:35.286 --> 00:36.321
I remember flying.

00:36.412 --> 00:38.323
l flewjets.
In the military, maybe.

00:38.414 --> 00:40.325
What's the first name
that pops into your head?

00:40.416 --> 00:41.781
Call me Nathan.

00:47.006 --> 00:48.041
l have a crush.

00:48.132 --> 00:49.167
(KNOCKING AT DOOR)

00:50.760 --> 00:53.547
Please accept this bid to join
the Psi Alpha Chi sisterhood.

00:54.347 --> 00:55.928
You need
to figure out how
to undo what you did,

00:56.015 --> 00:58.597
give me back my body,
and lwill be happy.

00:59.143 --> 01:01.304
You're a killer.
I'm a cop.

01:01.395 --> 01:04.728
If I have to keep you trapped
inside this prison
for the rest of my life,

01:04.815 --> 01:05.895
so be it.

01:08.402 --> 01:10.108
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

01:19.205 --> 01:20.820
(BOTH PANTING)

01:21.707 --> 01:23.163
(LAUGHS)

01:25.378 --> 01:27.835
(JANICE MOANING)

01:35.346 --> 01:37.428
(CONTINUES MOANING)

01:52.989 --> 01:56.481
That was amazing.
You were amazing.

02:03.040 --> 02:04.826
Forbidden fruit.

02:09.005 --> 02:10.541
My favorite kind.

02:46.042 --> 02:47.248
Sheriff,

02:48.377 --> 02:49.457
you can't do this.

02:49.545 --> 02:50.830
Is that right?

02:50.921 --> 02:55.335
Well, now, you say
you're a family friend,
and now you're a lawyer?

02:55.426 --> 02:56.882
Jeremy lost his parents.

02:56.969 --> 02:58.470
Well, my point exactly.

02:58.554 --> 03:00.340
You saw the broken heater
in that house.

03:00.431 --> 03:02.342
You can't lock him up
like he's some kind
of a killer.

03:02.433 --> 03:03.673
You know
this was an accident.

03:03.768 --> 03:08.683
Yeah. What I know is
that two people are dead,
and that boy...

03:08.773 --> 03:13.733
Well, let'sjust say that
it's not the first time he's
made some trouble in my town.

03:13.819 --> 03:16.071
Okay? He's building up
quite the rap sheet.

03:16.155 --> 03:17.520
Are you pressing charges?

03:17.615 --> 03:20.823
That kid ain't going
anywhere until I finish
my investigation.

03:20.910 --> 03:23.276
And if and when
that happens,

03:24.288 --> 03:27.530
I'm not releasing him
to anyone who's not
the next of kin.

03:27.625 --> 03:31.209
And that is
not you, friend.

03:32.338 --> 03:35.080
You have yourself
a nice evening now.

03:39.053 --> 03:40.042
(DOOR CLOSING)

03:40.471 --> 03:41.802
(PHONE BEEPS)

03:43.974 --> 03:45.134
Hey. It's me.

03:46.310 --> 03:47.811
I need your help.

04:16.924 --> 04:19.586
(LAUGHS) I can get
a latte here,
no problem, right?

04:19.677 --> 04:21.338
I saw a cow
about a mile back.

04:21.429 --> 04:23.670
You get some espresso,
we're in business.

04:23.764 --> 04:25.755
Thanks for coming.
I didn't know if you'd show.

04:25.850 --> 04:27.260
And who was your fallback?

04:27.351 --> 04:28.557
Don't have one.

04:28.853 --> 04:30.263
Then I'm honored.

04:30.938 --> 04:33.975
So, you found
a kid with abilities.

04:34.859 --> 04:36.975
I thought that you were
done with the whole
bag and tag business.

04:37.069 --> 04:39.776
This is more
of a rescue mission.

04:39.864 --> 04:41.775
His name is Jeremy,
17 years old.

04:41.866 --> 04:46.826
He has what you'd call
a dual ability.
Life and death.

04:46.912 --> 04:49.449
He got into an argument
with his parents and...

04:52.251 --> 04:53.536
His emotions got
the better of him.

04:53.627 --> 04:54.878
We all know that
that can happen.

04:55.588 --> 04:56.873
Is that why
you called me?

04:58.424 --> 05:00.335
Not entirely.

05:00.426 --> 05:02.508
Look, they won't
release him to me
because I'm not family.

05:02.595 --> 05:08.090
But it turns out that
the kid is very fond
of his Aunt Tracy.

05:10.603 --> 05:13.811
Just go in,
talk to him,
sign him out.

05:15.774 --> 05:18.060
I don't know.
He's got nobody.

05:19.487 --> 05:21.148
(SIGHS)
You've been there.

06:00.277 --> 06:01.778
Are you awake?

06:02.905 --> 06:05.317
Yeah. You?

06:05.407 --> 06:06.533
CLAIRE: Yep.

06:07.660 --> 06:11.369
Are you afraid I'm going
to kiss-attack you
in your sleep?

06:14.166 --> 06:15.326
Maybe.

06:21.298 --> 06:22.879
We should talk about this.

06:26.345 --> 06:28.461
Yeah, I guess we should.

06:30.182 --> 06:31.388
(EXHALES)

06:33.686 --> 06:35.222
(SIGHS)

06:37.147 --> 06:40.765
It was stupid
and impulsive and bad...

06:40.859 --> 06:42.360
It wasn't bad.

06:43.445 --> 06:47.438
I mean,
you're a good kisser,
ljust...

06:48.951 --> 06:51.033
I don't want
to mess this up.

06:51.453 --> 06:52.863
Mess what up?

06:52.955 --> 06:55.617
My new,
totally ordinary life.

06:56.500 --> 06:59.367
You know, the one
I'm still chasing.

06:59.461 --> 07:03.295
Gretch, you're the first
real friend I've had
since I left Texas,

07:03.382 --> 07:06.340
and that's
a big deal for me.

07:08.012 --> 07:10.003
And I really
like you a lot.

07:10.889 --> 07:13.881
Just not in that way.

07:21.025 --> 07:22.356
(GRUNTS)

07:27.823 --> 07:28.903
Jeez, Claire.

07:28.991 --> 07:31.698
You don't have to go
all Buffy on us.
We're just kidnapping you.

07:31.785 --> 07:33.992
(PANTING)
I am so sorry.

07:34.580 --> 07:36.912
Do you wanna be
an Alpha Chi or not?

07:37.750 --> 07:39.456
Is that
a trick question?

07:39.543 --> 07:40.908
Where are you taking us?

07:41.003 --> 07:43.369
Well, if I told you,
that wouldn't be

07:43.464 --> 07:45.546
a very good kidnapping,
would it?

07:54.892 --> 07:58.476
CLAIRE: I cannot believe
that they shoved us
in a trunk.

07:58.562 --> 07:59.847
So lame.

08:06.695 --> 08:07.901
Look at us.

08:08.739 --> 08:10.730
All tied up in the dark.

08:11.533 --> 08:14.900
You know, they have
entire websites
devoted to this.

08:18.415 --> 08:19.916
Sorry.
Sorry.

08:22.378 --> 08:23.914
(SIGHS)

08:24.880 --> 08:30.000
So, you were saying
how you didn't really
like me in that way.

08:30.094 --> 08:33.211
No, you were saying that.

08:34.390 --> 08:37.382
l was saying
that you've been
a great friend.

08:39.561 --> 08:42.644
So, which way is it?

08:46.568 --> 08:48.024
I don't know.

08:49.905 --> 08:51.645
What does that mean?

08:56.704 --> 08:58.615
It means I don't know.

08:59.123 --> 09:00.784
(CAR STOPS)

09:01.500 --> 09:02.956
Awesome.

09:04.795 --> 09:07.377
Good morning.
Welcome to Hell Week.

09:08.465 --> 09:09.875
All right, ladies,
listen up.

09:09.967 --> 09:14.051
This is what we call
a Screamin' Scavenger Hunt.

09:14.138 --> 09:16.595
There's a big Alpha Chi
treasure close by.

09:16.682 --> 09:20.220
Whichever team finds it first
gets to sit out Hell Week.

09:20.310 --> 09:23.598
Trust me,
you wanna sit out.
We bought goldfish.

09:23.689 --> 09:26.226
(SORORITY GIRLS LAUGH)
Good luck.

09:26.525 --> 09:27.731
But remember, ladies,

09:27.818 --> 09:30.981
someone's gotta win
and someone's gotta lose.

09:31.071 --> 09:32.527
(SORORITY GIRLS SCREAM)

09:36.160 --> 09:37.400
(DOOR SLAMS)

09:37.494 --> 09:40.201
ASHLEY: Oh, my God.
Oh, my God.
Where are we?

09:56.680 --> 09:58.136
Thank you.

09:59.391 --> 10:00.801
Jeremy.

10:06.190 --> 10:08.806
My name's Tracy.
I'm a friend
of Mr. Bennet's.

10:09.860 --> 10:11.441
How'd you get in here?

10:11.528 --> 10:13.814
TRACY: We told them
that l was your aunt.

10:13.906 --> 10:15.021
My aunt?

10:16.200 --> 10:17.906
I don't have an aunt.

10:18.410 --> 10:19.911
You do now.

10:19.995 --> 10:23.362
Mr. Bennet fixed
some papen/vork,
and here I am.

10:24.541 --> 10:28.159
Mr. Bennet said that
everything would go away,

10:29.546 --> 10:31.923
that the cops
would buy the story.

10:33.342 --> 10:38.553
Mr. Bennet said
they'd let me go.

10:39.014 --> 10:40.220
Hey.

10:43.435 --> 10:45.847
All I have to do
is sign you out.

10:46.396 --> 10:48.773
That might not be
such a good idea.

10:48.857 --> 10:50.017
Why not?

10:55.697 --> 10:58.734
I killed my parents.
I'm a murderer.

11:02.246 --> 11:04.487
You can't control me.
You've never been
able to do that.

11:04.581 --> 11:06.367
Well, I had
a compelling reason.

11:06.458 --> 11:08.369
Let's face it.
Your wife is kind of hot.

11:08.460 --> 11:09.870
(SHOUTS) Enough.

11:09.962 --> 11:13.079
That's the second Parkman
I made scream today.

11:14.508 --> 11:15.714
(LAUGHS)

11:15.801 --> 11:18.588
If you want,
I can give you
some pointers later.

11:18.720 --> 11:20.256
You crazy psycho.

11:22.766 --> 11:27.305
What are you gonna do?
Hit me?
Defend your lady's honor?

11:27.437 --> 11:29.769
We both know
it's not about that.

11:31.108 --> 11:36.193
It's about
all those other things
I can do to her and Matty.

11:36.280 --> 11:38.987
The next time
I take over your body,

11:53.797 --> 11:55.207
(ELECTRICITY CRACKLING)

11:55.632 --> 11:56.667
Hmm.

11:56.758 --> 11:58.089
Cozy.

12:02.139 --> 12:04.221
Oh, my God.
Do you smell that?

12:04.308 --> 12:06.799
It smells like
something died in here.

12:07.185 --> 12:08.766
OLIVIA:
What is this place?

12:08.854 --> 12:10.344
Oh, my God.

12:11.023 --> 12:12.479
Slaughterhouse.

12:13.275 --> 12:14.936
Oh, my...

12:15.027 --> 12:17.143
Please don't say that again.

12:19.656 --> 12:20.987
Hey, guys.

12:21.575 --> 12:24.487
Super-cute puzzle over here.

12:29.082 --> 12:31.869
GRETCHEN: "What you find
will help you survive.

12:31.960 --> 12:34.576
"When we were found
will keep you alive."

12:34.671 --> 12:35.922
"When we were found"?

12:36.006 --> 12:38.918
Okay, guys,
let's just open one so
we can get out of here.

12:39.009 --> 12:40.249
CLAIRE: Wait.

12:44.640 --> 12:45.755
(SCREAMING)

12:48.518 --> 12:50.429
Relax. Relax.
It's not real.

12:50.520 --> 12:52.021
They're just trying
to scare us.

12:56.526 --> 12:57.936
(ASHLEY SIGHS)

12:58.862 --> 13:00.193
Open 24.

13:00.989 --> 13:02.104
How do you know?

13:02.199 --> 13:06.067
"When we were found."
1924. That's when
the sorority was founded.

13:06.161 --> 13:07.947
You know that?

13:08.038 --> 13:10.529
My mom's a former sister,
remember?

13:11.833 --> 13:13.209
(SIGHS)

13:18.590 --> 13:19.796
Oh.

13:20.384 --> 13:21.544
(CLAIRE LAUGHS)
Yayl

13:23.679 --> 13:25.135
Thank God.
I am so thirsty.

13:25.222 --> 13:27.463
Hey. One bottle per team.

13:28.558 --> 13:32.392
No problem. Come on, Ash.
They won the first round.

13:32.479 --> 13:34.595
Now we are going
to bring it.

13:34.690 --> 13:36.646
(WHINES) Can I
just stay here?

13:39.194 --> 13:40.400
Jeremy,

13:41.613 --> 13:44.571
what happened
with your parents,

13:45.492 --> 13:47.073
I understand.

13:48.578 --> 13:50.569
All you did
was touch them.

13:52.332 --> 13:56.575
The day that
I discovered my ability,
I killed a man.

13:57.921 --> 13:59.502
He was threatening me.

13:59.589 --> 14:04.208
I grabbed him,
and something took over,

14:04.928 --> 14:06.429
something inside of me.

14:11.268 --> 14:13.259
And no matter
how hard I tried...

14:14.730 --> 14:16.766
You couldn't let go.

14:19.776 --> 14:23.234
Your emotions took over.
You got mad.

14:23.321 --> 14:25.482
For most people,
that's not a bad thing.

14:28.118 --> 14:29.779
We're not most people.

14:31.288 --> 14:32.778
(CRIES)

14:33.790 --> 14:35.872
I'm gonna get you
out of here.

14:41.798 --> 14:43.004
His next of kin is here.

14:43.091 --> 14:45.082
What possible reason
do you have
for holding him?

14:45.177 --> 14:47.042
Well, we got plenty.

14:47.137 --> 14:48.217
Is this Jeremy's?

14:49.681 --> 14:52.297
Gil, show him
what we found.

14:55.020 --> 14:59.229
"I feel the darkness
surrounding me.
I am the bringer of death."

14:59.316 --> 15:00.556
He's 17 years old.

15:00.650 --> 15:02.481
Half the songs on his iPod
sound just like that.

15:02.569 --> 15:04.855
Well, maybe I should
read you the part
about killing animals.

15:04.946 --> 15:07.403
Any kid at school
will tell you he does it.
For fun.

15:07.491 --> 15:10.278
So now we're taking
gossip as evidence?
Is that it?

15:10.368 --> 15:13.155
There's something wrong
with that boy, okay?

15:13.246 --> 15:15.328
As far as I'm concerned,
this proves it.

15:15.415 --> 15:19.158
He ain't getting away
with killing his family.
He's staying right here.

15:23.465 --> 15:25.626
TRACY: No. They still
haven't charged him

15:25.717 --> 15:28.003
and their evidence is
circumstantial at best.

15:29.304 --> 15:30.840
Yes, right now.

15:32.265 --> 15:34.677
I'm calling in
a favor, Dennis.

15:35.852 --> 15:38.514
Thank you. All right,
I'll see you then.

15:41.191 --> 15:44.149
Sounds like you're
shaking things up
in there.

15:44.861 --> 15:46.772
From the looks of the place,
I'd say they could use it.

15:47.614 --> 15:48.694
Is that right?

15:48.782 --> 15:53.116
Tell me something.
How's a girl like you
end up in a place like this?

15:53.203 --> 15:54.864
(LAUGHS) You'd have
to do better than that.

15:54.955 --> 15:58.413
The name is Samuel.
And I'm here to
ask you one question.

15:58.500 --> 16:02.960
If you're here to save
young Jeremy's life,
then what's next?

16:04.464 --> 16:07.001
Are you gonna take him
to a place just to live?

16:11.138 --> 16:13.845
(CARNIVAL MUSIC PLAYING)

16:16.977 --> 16:18.888
(PEOPLE CHATTERING)

16:22.440 --> 16:24.305
Or where he belongs?

16:27.696 --> 16:28.651
What did you do?

16:28.738 --> 16:29.773
It's all right.

16:29.865 --> 16:30.820
Stay back.

16:30.907 --> 16:32.647
I'm a friend, Tracy.

16:33.660 --> 16:34.820
How do you know
my name?

16:34.911 --> 16:36.742
It's all right.
You're safe here.

16:36.830 --> 16:39.993
I'm like you.
We're all like you.

16:42.252 --> 16:43.367
What is this place?

16:45.046 --> 16:46.206
Home.

16:56.683 --> 16:59.925
Slaughter floor
or operations center?

17:00.729 --> 17:02.219
CLAIRE: Should I even ask?

17:02.981 --> 17:04.767
Have a nice Hell Week.

17:12.824 --> 17:14.155
After you.

17:21.958 --> 17:23.573
CLAIRE: Ugh.

17:29.299 --> 17:31.085
So, how long
have you known?

17:31.176 --> 17:35.089
Known what?
That I really don't wanna
be in this sorority?

17:35.639 --> 17:37.425
That you liked girls.

17:37.641 --> 17:38.801
(LAUGHS)

17:38.892 --> 17:41.508
You make it sound
like I have to declare.

17:41.603 --> 17:43.639
Like it's my major
or something.

17:44.689 --> 17:46.645
I'm actually jealous.

17:47.234 --> 17:51.068
First year of college
and you've already
figured yourself out.

17:51.696 --> 17:53.436
I don't know about that.

17:53.531 --> 17:56.113
Truth is, I've had
more boyfriends
than girlfriends.

17:56.243 --> 17:57.449
Really?
Mmm-hmm.

17:58.453 --> 17:59.954
How many more?

18:01.790 --> 18:04.497
Six or seven.
It's not a lot, right?

18:06.086 --> 18:07.792
Sounds about right.

18:08.880 --> 18:10.586
But you're not...

18:10.674 --> 18:13.507
No, you couldn't be.
You were a cheerleader.

18:13.593 --> 18:14.833
Not what?

18:15.512 --> 18:16.752
A virgin.

18:16.846 --> 18:18.711
(LAUGHS)

18:18.807 --> 18:20.763
(LAUGHS) Wow.

18:21.393 --> 18:23.600
We could not be
more different.

18:23.687 --> 18:25.973
Maybe we're
strange attractors.

18:26.398 --> 18:28.013
Strange attractors?

18:28.400 --> 18:29.936
It's a physics thing.

18:30.026 --> 18:32.278
Everything in the universe
has a magnetic charge, right?

18:32.362 --> 18:34.318
So strange attractors
are particles

18:34.406 --> 18:36.522
that end up together
that don't really
belong together,

18:36.616 --> 18:39.153
but when they're together,
they're super powerful.

18:39.244 --> 18:41.360
Sort of like
we could be.

18:42.580 --> 18:43.911
Or not.

18:44.249 --> 18:45.409
What?

18:46.084 --> 18:47.290
Hold on.

18:50.088 --> 18:53.421
Come on. Don't tell me
you're freaked out now.

18:54.217 --> 18:56.082
I mean, look. See?

18:56.928 --> 18:58.213
Nothing.

18:59.389 --> 19:01.380
Just more lameness.

19:02.976 --> 19:04.307
Gretch.

19:08.398 --> 19:10.059
What the hell was that?

19:12.444 --> 19:13.559
(GRUNTS)

19:13.653 --> 19:16.144
I'm starting to think
this isn't a game.

19:16.239 --> 19:18.480
This is the life
Jeremy could have.

19:18.575 --> 19:20.907
What? Working
at a carnival?

19:21.244 --> 19:24.577
Surrounded by family.
His true family.

19:29.336 --> 19:32.328
Do you remember the first time
you experienced your gift?

19:32.422 --> 19:35.164
"Gift" might be
a little generous.

19:35.258 --> 19:39.217
Like the entire universe
coursing through you,
all at once.

19:39.304 --> 19:41.795
That wasn't just
your ability, Tracy.

19:42.682 --> 19:45.845
You were tapping
into something
greater than yourself.

19:58.698 --> 20:00.154
SAMUEL:
We're all connected.

20:00.658 --> 20:01.693
TRACY: I'd like
to believe that.

20:01.785 --> 20:02.865
BeHeveit

20:02.952 --> 20:07.366
Every time someone
joins this family,
| get a feeling, in here.

20:07.457 --> 20:08.742
It's an energy, I guess.

20:08.833 --> 20:12.041
It gets stronger every day.
This is where
Jeremy should be.

20:12.629 --> 20:15.245
What, living in trailers?
Drifting from town to town?

20:15.340 --> 20:18.377
What would you do?
Give him a false name?
A false life?

20:19.135 --> 20:22.468
This is a boy
who can work miracles.
Why should he be invisible?

20:24.307 --> 20:27.140
Bring him home.
You could join him.

20:28.520 --> 20:31.887
I know you've been lost, too.
It's your nature.

20:31.981 --> 20:33.357
That's enough.

20:34.943 --> 20:36.854
Just take me back now.

20:37.654 --> 20:38.894
Fair enough.

20:41.491 --> 20:44.153
Look, I'm never
about the hard sell,
but please take this.

20:44.661 --> 20:47.152
To find your way back here.

20:51.501 --> 20:53.162
This is Lydia.

20:54.212 --> 20:55.998
